==English==

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|bʰeydʰ}}
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|abiden}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|ābīdan||to abide, wait, remain, delay, remain behind; survive; wait for, await; expect}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*uzbīdaną||to expect, tolerate}}, equivalent to {{prefix|a|bide|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|abyde||to abide, remain}}, {{cog|gmh|erbīten||to await, expect}}, {{cog|got|𐌿𐍃𐌱𐌴𐌹𐌳𐌰𐌽||to expect, await, have patience}}. The sense of ''pay for'' is due to influence from {{m|en|aby}}.<ref>{{R:MW3 1976|page=3}}</ref>

